        "id": 1003211
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-14T23:11:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Isn\u0027t the default case in your example !matches(s.Name, names) \u0026\u0026 !matches(s.Rack, racks) \u0026\u0026 !matches(s.Datacenter, datacenters)? The default would only be reached if the three matches cases all failed. I think I would need:\n\nswitch {\ncase !matches(s.Name, names):\n  // Doesn\u0027t match names filter.\ncase !matches(s.Rack, racks):\n  // Doesn\u0027t match racks filter.\ncase !matches(s.Datacenter, datacenters):\n  // Doesn\u0027t match datacenters filter.\ndefault:\n  // Doesn\u0027t match any of the above cases (meaning it matches all filters).\n  switches \u003d append(switches, s)\n}\n\nIs that wrong?\n\nAt any rate I\u0027m okay with the line length for the time being.",
      "parentUuid": "bd3f74c2_65dfdc6a",
      "revId": "ee4c73556482b653e1673c3a9e4983229e657d87",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
